            • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

              I think Jeu is a Spurs fan. Anyways, I fancy them to win in this "no win" fixture for a Gooner. The 5-3 last season at the Lane, when Chelsea were playing well I might add, stopped the general Chelsea dominance in this fixture and I'm sure the Spurs attack will be buoyed by Chelsea's defensive ineptitude thus far. Alli is a big miss for Spurs, and I expect Mason to play in his place as he is more defensively astute than Dembele. If Spurs can get Son, Eriksen and Lamela (providing he's fit) working like a classic Brazilian 3 behind Kane then I fancy them to score 2 or 3. You can never rule Chelsea out, regardless of how badly they seemingly play. Hazard at his best can create a chance out of nowhere (and buy 1 or 2 free kicks...) and Willian is up there with the best free-kick takers in world football atm (Eriksen up there too incidentally). An early Spurs goal will prevent the big blue bus being rolled out so hoping that happens, I'll say 3-2 Spurs. Painful to say.
